# Agent skills — see CONTRIBUTING.md "Agent skills".
# Native (hand-authored) skills are committed; everything else (vendored skills
# from skills-lock.json) is restored with `make skills-restore`, so its content
# AND generated .claude/skills symlinks stay out of git. Ignore all, keep only
# native — so adjusting the lock never touches this file; only a NEW native
# skill adds two `!` lines. .gitattributes marks .agents as linguist-vendored.
.agents/skills/*
!.agents/skills/cubeplex-tdd/
!.agents/skills/debug-cubeplex/
!.agents/skills/feature-workflow/
!.agents/skills/pr-codex-review-loop/
.claude/skills/*
!.claude/skills/cubeplex-tdd
!.claude/skills/debug-cubeplex
!.claude/skills/feature-workflow
!.claude/skills/pr-codex-review-loop
.superpowers/
settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
backend/.claude/


